verbose_text: When subjects were stratified by BMI and parity, there was a difference in average salivary 17beta-estradiol levels throughout the entire menstrual cycle between the four groups of women (P = 0.016, age adjusted) : parous women with BMI> = 25 kg/m 2 had a higher average daily level of salivary 17beta-estradiol throughout the entire menstrual cycle compared with both nulliparous women (P = 0.021, age adjusted) and parous women (P = 0.018, age adjusted) with BMI < 25 kg/m 2.
